cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.RO 

This paper deals with multiple agents moving in a graph and making decisions based on their goals and the actions of their opponents. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of area protection involves strategic decision making and game theory (cs.GT). The use of graphs and vertex allocation strategies involves data structures (cs.DS) and robotics (cs.RO).
